      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AUDENZIA (1) racing well this prep and due for a change of luck. Sat on the speed from the wide draw and kept finding with a narrow second over 1500m at Kembla Grange. Can take the sit here and pounce late with the fast tempo. ISHIKARI (2) exciting mare in career best form. Proved her win at Orange was no fluke two-back, with a sharp on-pace victory over 1400m at Randwick in Highway class. Gets a better set-up for this and is expected to go close. BENAMERA (5) rounded up a good field with ease three starts back over the 1400m at Newcastle. Dropped in grade when he raced handy to score a comfortable win over 1300m at Canberra. Big weight drop and stays in the calculations. BLOW IN (8) tough old customer who won't know himself with the 52kg. Drifted back on the quick back-up with a battling sixth over 1400m at Bathurst. Goes into the exotics.",
